[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] Indeed, the mapping ⊗ is called *canonical*, or more explicitly: the canonical mapping (or balanced product) of the tensor product.
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] The definition does not prove the existence of *M* ⊗*R* *N*; see below for a construction.
