[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] Analogously, if *N* has a right action by a ring *S*, then $M\otimes _{R}N$ becomes a right *S*-module.
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] The resulting map is surjective since pure tensors *x* ⊗ *y* generate the whole module.
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] In particular, taking *R* to be $\mathbb {Z}$ this shows every tensor product of modules is a quotient of a tensor product of abelian groups.
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] It is possible to extend the definition to a tensor product of any number of modules over the same commutative ring.
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] The binary tensor product is associative: (*M*1 ⊗ *M*2) ⊗ *M*3 is naturally isomorphic to *M*1 ⊗ (*M*2 ⊗ *M*3).
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] The tensor product of three modules defined by the universal property of trilinear maps is isomorphic to both of these iterated tensor products.
