[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] Because of this, $-\otimes _{R}S$ is often called the extension of scalars from *R* to *S*.
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] In representation theory, when *R*, *S* are group algebras, the above relation becomes Frobenius reciprocity.
[src:module-theory/tensor-product-of-modules] The structure of a tensor product of quite ordinary modules may be unpredictable.
